To solve this problem, we need to process a string `s` consisting of lowercase letters and special characters (`'*'`, `'#'`, `'%'`) according to specific rules to construct a new string `result`. The goal is to return the k-th character (0-indexed) of the resulting string after processing all characters in `s`. If `k` is out of bounds, we return `'.'`.

### Approach
